0008               * Floating point numbers are in RADIX 100 format.
0009               * Details: https://www.unige.ch/medecine/nouspikel/ti99/reals.htm#Radix%20100
0010               *
0011               *
0012               * Drive/Device catalog format:
0013               *
0014               *    RECORD 0 -> volume label and device information
0015               *
0016               *    hex   01234567
0017               *    0008  ........
0018               *    0010  ........
0019               *    0018  ........
0020               *    0020  ........
0021               *    0028  ........
0022               *    0030  ........
0023               *    0038  ........
0024               *
0025               *
0026               *    RECORD 1...n -> file and directory information
0027               *
0028               *    hex   01234567
0029               *    0008  ABLSSSSS
0030               *    0010  SSSSSS1E
0031               *    0018  MMMMMMM2
0032               *    0020  EMMMMMMM
0033               *    0028  3EMMMMMM
0034               *    0030  M.......
0035               *
0036               *    A=>00 \ Record size 38 bytes (>26) or 146 bytes (>92).
0037               *    B=>26 / Note: only 146 bytes if device supports timestamps.
0038               *    L=>xx String length (max. >0A)
0039               *    S=>xx String ASCII char (filename)
0040               *
0041               *    1=>08 Float size     1 byte
0042               *    E=>xx Float exponent 1 byte
0043               *    M=>xx Float mantissa 7 bytes
0044               *    	1 - Record type:
0045               *    		0 = Volume label
0046               *    		1 = File type Display/Fixed
0047               *    		2 = File type Display/Variable
0048               *    		3 = File type Internal/Fixed
0049               *    		4 = File type Internal/Variable
0050               *    		5 = File type Program (binary)
0051               *    		6 = Directory
0052               *    		If a file type < 0 it means that the file is write protected.
0053               *
0054               *    2=>08 Float 2 size
0055               *    F=>xx Float 8 bytes
0056               *    	2 - If Record type is Volume label (0): Size of the device in 256 bytes
0057               *    	                                        sectors
0058               *    	    If Record type is File type  (1-5): Number of 256 bytes sectors the
0059               *    	                                        file occupies
0060               *    	    If Record type is Directory   (6) : Number of 256 bytes sectors the
0061               *    	                                        directory index occupies
0062               *    	                                        (2*sectors/alocation unit) but
0063               *    	                                        some peripherals just returns 0!
0064               *
0065               *    3=>08 Float 3 size
0066               *    F=>xx Float 8 bytes
0067               *    	3 - If Record type is Volume label (0): Number of free 256 bytes sectors
0068               *    	    If Record type is File type  (1-4): Maximum record length of file
0069               *    	    If Record type is Program file (5): The value 0, but on some
0070               *    	                                        peripherals the size in bytes!
0071               *    	    If Record type is Directory    (6): The value 0
0072               *===============================================================================
